channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: WATCH: Woke Aussie Olympic Break Dancer Puts On a Laughable Show; But, Here's a Real Athlete
Trump accuses Harris of 'stealing' his no tax on tips promise after her campus rally in Las Vegas
item.description: Former President Trump accused Vice President Kamala Harris for 'stealing' his no tax on tips policy after she parroted the same policy at a rally in Las Vegas.

item.title: Newsom's Office Paying Famous Photographer $200K a Year
item.description: California Gov. Gavin Newsom's office hired a famous photographer on a $200,000 yearly salary six months ago, Politico reported Saturday.

item.title: Gov. Photo Op: Gavin Newsom Hires $200K a Year Photographer, Bet You Can Guess Who Pays the Bill
Harris voters defend Democratic presidential nominee on Israel-Hamas conflict: ‘She’s married to a Jewish guy’
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris' stance on Israel and Gaza has been at the fore in recent weeks. Fox News Digital questioned rallygoers in Arizona and Nevada about her policy platform.

item.title: Rep. Fischbach to Newsmax: Vegas Emergency Call on Biden Raises Questions
item.description: An audio recording released Friday concerning an emergency call about President Joe Biden when he was in Las Vegas days before he stepped out of the presidential campaign, raises questions about who is running the country, Rep. Michelle Fischbach said.

item.title: NEW: Internal Tensions Roil Kamala Harris Campaign Even As Press Declares Nothing But 'Joy'
Newsom cleans up homeless California encampments after he allocated billions of dollars while crisis grew
item.description: Newsom cleaned up trash from homeless encampments in Los Angeles and warned municipalities they’ll lose state funding if they don’t do more to clear them across the state.

item.title: Rep. Jack Bergman to Newsmax: Walz Engaged in 'an Intent to Deceive'
item.description: Rep. Jack Bergman, R-Mich., told Newsmax on Saturday that Gov. Tim Walz's previous statement on his military record were "an intent to deceive."

item.title: CONSEQUENCES: Pro-Hamas Demonstrators Who Blocked Golden Gate Bridge Hit With Multiple Charges
Las Vegas rideshare drivers laud Trump’s ‘awesome’ no-tax-on-tips plan as Harris holds rally across town
item.description: Rideshare drivers across Las Vegas voiced support for former President Trump's stated plan to end taxation of gratuities to lessen inflation's blow on service industry workers.

item.title: Biden Exited '24 Race to Keep Focus on Trump, Unite Nation
item.description: Joe Biden withdrew from the 2024 presidential race because he needed to keep the nation's focus on Trump and unite the Democratic Party, the president told CBS News Sunday Morning.

item.title: Venezuelan Dictator Maduro Curtly Rejects Safe Passage Offer From Panamanian President
Minnesota teacher pension fund under Walz accused of 'cooking the books' with unrealistic gains: report
item.description: Under Gov. Walz, Minnesota’s Teachers Retirement Association is accused by a pension investigator of hiding fees and reporting implausibly high returns, termed a "Madoff miracle."

item.title: Harris Vows to Back Fed Independence
item.description: U.S. Vice President Kamala Harris said on Saturday the Federal Reserve is independent and she would never interfere in its decisions if she wins the Nov. 5 presidential election.
